examples.content:
Cut 1/4 block or 3 ounces of fresh tofu into large cubes (about 1 in x 1 in) and pat it dry with a towel. Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil to a non-stick pan and add the tofu cubes and a few pinches of salt. Turn on the heat to medium-high. Cook 5 to 6 minutes until lightly browned on the bottom. Briefly remove the pan from the heat to reduce spitting. Flip the tofu with tongs. Return the heat to medium-high and cook until browned. Briefly remove from the heat again and drizzle with the 1 tablespoons sesame oil and 1 tablespoon soy sauce (watch for spitting). Return to low heat and cook 2 minutes, then flip and cook 2 minutes until the colour is darkened. Serve immediately."
